# Rasm Analysis And Domain

Read `libs/csharp/Rasm/AGENTS.md` before edits.

## Ownership

| Folder | Owns |
| --- | --- |
| `Domain/` | `Context`, tolerances, geometry kind, coercion, ownership, validity, requirements, faults, stats, residuals, distributions, acceptance, and projection carriers. |
| `Analysis/` | `Analyze`, `Operation<TGeometry,TOut>`, `IAspect`, and higher-order geometry analysis built on `Domain`. |

## Rules

- Extend existing `Domain` owners before adding local validation, stats, geometry-kind, or coercion logic.
- Keep `Domain` independent of `Analysis`, `Vectors`, and future concern folders.
- Route analysis through the unified `Analyze`/operation surface instead of per-file consumer APIs.
- Model new intent as typed records, smart enums, unions, or projection carriers when it reduces primitive knobs.
- Keep native interop converted at the boundary into typed rails and receipts.

## Validation

Run `bash scripts/check-cs.sh check`. Add `bash scripts/test.sh` when behavior or test oracles change.
